Chances are that if you're reading this, you're an actionscripter.
Please email any code patches/suggestions you think of!
What follows is a breakdown of the structure of openSIMS.


FILE                          DESCRIPTION
----------------------------------------------------------------------
openSIMS.flp			Flash project file with all .fla's

index.fla			Loads in bulk of global codebase
- navbar.as			Buttons and layout
- global_config.as		Reads config.xml and globalizes values	
- global_lib.as			Functions used throughout
- global_styles.as		Font style formats for dynamic text
- socket_lib.as			Handles connections to Java socket
- DynTween.as			Tatsuo Kato's tweening prototypes
- DynColorTween.as		see http://www.tatsuokato.com	
- FDraggableWindow.as		Component code for windows
- LS_FScrollPane.as		Modified scrollpane for FDraggableWindow

components_lib.fla/swf		All shared components/fonts

live.fla/swf (live.as)		Live visualization, loads live.as
- live_config.as		openSIMS specific functions
- live_ATKDEF.as		Attacker/Defender specific functions

plugin_test.fla/swf		Flash plugin test output

reports.fla/swf (reports.as)	Reports page

support.fla/swf (support.as)	Support page	